ssccrriipptt -- Command

Capture a terminal session into a file
ssccrriipptt [-ll _l_o_g_f_i_l_e] [_c_o_m_m_a_n_d]

The  COHERENT command  ssccrriipptt executes _c_o_m_m_a_n_d  while copying  all terminal
output  to  _l_o_g_f_i_l_e.  _l_o_g_f_i_l_e defaults  to  file  LLoogg._p_i_d  in your  current
directory, where _p_i_d is the  number of the recording process.  _c_o_m_m_a_n_d must
specify a  full path name.   If the terminal echoes  keyboard input, ssccrriipptt
records these keystrokes in _l_o_g_f_i_l_e.

If  no  _c_o_m_m_a_n_d is  specified,  ssccrriipptt executes  the  command specified  by
environmental variable  SSHHEELLLL by default.  If SSHHEELLLL  is not defined, ssccrriipptt
assumes /bbiinn/sshh.

To exit from ssccrriipptt, just type eexxiitt from a command prompt.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
ccoommmmaannddss

_N_o_t_e_s
ssccrriipptt  is intended  to capture  what you type  for purposes  of debugging.
What it captures cannot be replayed into the shell.
